  "title": {
    "en": "Advanced pytest: Mocking & Monkeypatch",
    "ta": "மேம்பட்ட pytest: Mocking & Monkeypatch"
  },
  "description": {
    "en": "Learn to mock external dependencies, use monkeypatch for isolated tests, organize with conftest.py, and extend pytest with plugins.",
    "ta": "வெளிப்புற dependencies-ஐ mock செய்யவும், monkeypatch-உடன் isolated சோதனைகள் எழுதவும், conftest.py-உடன் ஒழுங்கமைக்கவும், plugins-உடன் pytest-ஐ விரிவாக்கவும் கற்றுக்கொள்ளுங்கள்."
  },
  "xp_reward": 65,
  "story_variants": {
    "en": "## Vaathiyaar's Stunt Double\n\nVaathiyaar shows a movie poster. \"In films, the hero doesn't jump off buildings — a stunt double does. In testing, when your code calls an API, database, or file system, you don't call the real thing. You use a **mock** — a stunt double for your dependencies.\"\n\n### Mocking with unittest.mock\n- `Mock()` — creates a fake object that records calls\n- `patch()` — replaces a real object with a mock temporarily\n- `MagicMock()` — Mock with magic methods pre-configured\n- `mock.return_value` — set what the mock returns\n\n### monkeypatch: pytest's Way\n- `monkeypatch.setattr()` — replace attributes/functions\n- `monkeypatch.setenv()` — set environment variables\n- `monkeypatch.delenv()` — remove environment variables\n- Automatically reverted after each test\n\n### conftest.py\n- Shared fixtures live in `conftest.py`\n- No import needed — pytest discovers it automatically\n- Can exist at multiple directory levels\n\n> **Key Concept:** Never let tests depend on external systems. Mock the boundary, test the logic. Your tests should pass even on an airplane with no internet."
  },
